vectorData.altText: 6. The measurement of the distance between the sacral promontory and top of the pubis symphysis is called the __________ ____________.

A woman’s ability to safely deliver vaginally is predicted by the size of her pelvic inlet and outlet. 
The size of the pelvic inlet is determined using measurements of the:
maximum transverse diameter of the inlet (A)
sagittal inlet (B), measured between the sacral promontory and the top of the pubic symphysis.

The size of the pelvic outlet is determined using measurements of the: 
bispinous outlet (C), the distance between the ischial spines, which is the narrowest lateral dimension of the birth canal
sagittal outlet (D), the distance between the coccyx and the bottom of the pubic symphysis
That’s right! This is the sagittal inlet.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.
